Requirements
- needs an active installation of Python 3.x (tested on 3.7)
- software needs to be installed in the same location for all users
- all PCs accessing the script need a unique name (name of the account that is logged in)
- textures need to use the following naming convention: channel.colour_space.udim.filetype
- texture channel names should not exceed 18 characters (this amount of space is allocated in the UIs)
- subdivisions and material assignments have to be set up in modelling

Limitations:
- no access restrictions for shows or assets can be given
- only windows compatibility has been tested
- needs to run a version of blender 2.91 or later (might work with 2.8 and later, but tested on 2.91)
